Uncountable nouns			- much, little
Plural nouns			  	- many, few

Uncountable and plural nouns 	  	- a lot of, lots of, plenty of
Negative sentences and questions 	- much, many

Positive sentences     			- a lot(Of) -note too much and so much is OK
(Much is unusual in positive sentences in spoken English. same goes with many)

Little and few (without a) are negative ideas (you can use very little and very few)

A little and a few are  positive ideas (only a little and only a few have a negative meaning)
